txt.en: 'Phew! I shall need a pause after that one.'
'Ha! There is life in me yet!'
'I will go! I just need a breather after that.'
'I am getting too old for this!'
'Ive won! What? Where is the rest of the food?'
'That ale was delicious! I could run forever.'
'My poor belly -- how heavy I feel!'
'Scrumptious! More, please!'
'Welcome to the Taste of Hobbiton! The race shall begin in three minutes.'
'Now, now, do not rush me. That was no dainty tea-cake!'
'Get set....'
'A moment, if you please, or I shall waddle the rest of the way....'
'Strong brew! I must walk this one off a bit.'
'Delicious! I cannot wait to sample more!'
'Whoop! That gave me some vigour!'
'The race shall commence in two minutes, my merry friends!'
'Just a moment, if you please! That was a stout one.'
'That smells wonderful!'
'Whoop! How I love food! I can't wait to try more.'
'Oof, that was a stout drink! Now I am weary... sluggishly trudgish.'
'Mmm, food!'
'That one froze the very hairs in my beard... I will be ready in a moment.'
'That one put some life in my legs! Here I come.'
'Life isn't fair!'
'Urp! Pardon me; I need a moment.'
'I won! Is there more food?'
'Food, here I come!'
'Hmph! You could not possibly expect me to run after such a meal.'
'Where is the rest? What? I won? Huzzah!'
'I was so close! So close.'
'Only one minute until the race begins....'
'One minute only until the Taste of Hobbiton commences!'
'Do not rush me! That was a heavy meal.'
'Noooooo! I was so close....'
'I won! But... but... I'm still hungry.'
'Goodness me, goodness me. I could not eat another bite just now....'
'Sometimes it is best to rest if you are stuffed.'
'Goodness me, that was hearty! I need a moment, if you please.'
'Nooooo....'
And they're off!
'Go, go!'
'On your mark....'
'I'm starving!'
'I am ready to burst after that! Why must this food be so heavy?'
'I am famished!'
'Ho-ho, I don't know if I can go on....'
